WHEREAS, transitional housing and support for homeless families on the path to self-
sufficiency are provided through Agape's homeless services, while Christ-centered counseling
for individuals, couples, families, and groups experiencing relationship conflicts, life crises, or
other issues is offered by the organization's counseling services; and
WHEREAS, Agape provides love, encouragement, and hope to those experiencing
unplanned pregnancies and considering adoption, as well as for those looking to adopt, through
the organization's adoption services; and
WHEREAS, Agape Child & Family Services has been a beacon of hope and support for
under-resourced populations in Memphis for fifty-five years, and it is fitting that we specially
recognize this exceptional organization on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Agape Child & Family Services and its staff
and volunteers on the occasion of the organization's fifty-fifth anniversary, extending our
deepest gratitude for their invaluable contributions to the Memphis community and our best
wishes for every continued success in their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
